1.title: Spring Breakers
1.plot: In the season premiere, Matt plans to take a secret detour while on a business trip to see his friend and country singer star Luke Bryan in concert. Suspicious that Matt might try to mix business with pleasure, Ryan sends T-Carr along to babysit. Meanwhile, Hard Luck has to face that his daughter, Jessa, is no longer just his baby girl.

2.title: Pitch Please
2.plot: Matt and Ryan hold a "pitch day" for potential Wildgame products but try to box out all of Hard Luck's crazy ideas. Will Hard Luck figure out a way to be heard? Meanwhile, Joe Buck starts working at the ranch with T-Carr and finds out that starting at the bottom is not as glamorous as he thought.

3.title: Urine or Ur-Out
3.plot: Matt decides to take dating seriously for the first time in 8 years and gets set up on a "real date." On the professional side of his life, Matt decides to take on the urine distribution market, but when T-Carr and Hard Luck crash the party will his urine dreams go down the drain?

4.title: Stand of Brothers
4.plot: Ryan wants to replace Hard Luck's ancient hunting stand with a new Wildgame Innovations stand, but Hard Luck refuses to let go. Meanwhile, Ryan tasks Matt to create a new bow fishing marketing video but Matt's urban vision clashes with Ryan's traditional marketing ideas.

5.title: Bachelor Bucks
5.plot: Matt and Ryan hold a "pitch day" for potential Wildgame products but try to box out all of Hard Luck's crazy ideas. Will Hard Luck figure out a way to be heard? Meanwhile, Joe Buck starts working at the ranch with T-Carr and finds out that starting at the bottom is not as glamorous as he thought.

6.title: Landry vs Busbice
6.plot: Matt, Ryan and Hard Luck head up to Lambeau Field for an event with Troy Landry. While in Green Bay, the Landry and Busbice competitive spirit is in full swing and it leads to a lot of smack-talk. The families decide to hold a competition back in Louisiana to determine who the best hunters are once and for all.

1.title: Sac-Attack
1.plot: While Willie Roberston and the Busbice boys are on their yearly pre-hunting season scout of the Busbice property, Big Bill finds that T-Carr left out a giant block of deer food that has now become infested with bees. Matt, T-Carr, and Ryan are then tasked with the mission to remove a giant "bee block." Meanwhile, the boy's crazy uncle Hard Luck is pursuing one of his most infamous ideas that he got while sitting on the toilet. Hard Luck recruits the help of his son Joe Buck and his wife Mona to help him create and test his underpants masterpiece!

2.title: Fishing Crossbow
2.plot: While out testing a new exploding target, Matt decides to create a new product that combines a crossbow and fishing reel system for the ultimate Fishing Crossbow. However, it's easier said than done, especially when he gets caught up babysitting for Ryan's kids while trying to construct it. Meanwhile, Ryan supervises T-Carr and Hard Luck as they try to "stinkify" themselves and redneck test a new hunting product.

3.title: Double Trouble
3.plot: Troy Landry the gator man of the south has come to the Busbices' lodge to "red neck field test" a new series of gator hunting products with Hard Luck. Meanwhile, Matt gets roped into a double date with Joe Buck.

4.title: Zipline
4.plot: While the boys are out hunting, Hard Luck hatches a plan to rig a zip line to a deer blind... an invention which he thinks will revolutionize the hunting industry. Meanwhile, Matt and T-Carr compete in an "Informerical-Off" to produce the better infomercial for the deer bait, Dirt Bag.

5.title: Jason Aldean
5.plot: Jason Aldean has come to the lodge for some much needed rest and relaxation from his tour and gets roped into hunting with Hard Luck. Meanwhile, Ryan gets pitched a new product from his church pastor in the local grocery store. And T-Carr and Bill put the pastor's product to the test.

6.title: Hard Luck Camo
6.plot: Hard Luck gets struck with another million-dollar idea and convinces T-Carr to jump aboard the crazy train to help make a new camouflage pattern that is anything but stealth. Meanwhile, Matt uses a new model of a trail camera and a robotic deer decoy to lure out poachers who have been lurking on the property.

7.title: Superdome
7.plot: Matt and Ryan are planning the most important party of their lives, promoting their award winning crossbow, at the Super Dome featuring their good friend, Willie Robertson. Instead of planning, Matt gets distracted trying to make one last update to the crossbow, against Ryan's wishes, and chaos ensues.

8.title: Recipe for Disaster
8.plot: When Hard Luck destroys Big Bill's favorite UTV, Matt and T-Carr decide to pimp out his new one with some top-notch gadgets. Meanwhile, Hard Luck attempts to revolutionize the deer feed market at the expense of Miss Beth's kitchen.

imdb.plot outline: Country Buck$ follows the Busbice family who founded Wildgame Innovations, a small hunting gear business that has grown into a multi-million dollar wildlife sporting empire. The company was launched more than a decade ago when brothers Ryan and Matt Busbice invented their first product, a deer feed block, on their home stove.
